shearing paddock
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a paddock where sheep are held for shearing. usually adjacent to a woolshed.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
